Reasoning: The paper is about transfer learning in computer vision, specifically evaluating the relationship between architecture and transfer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of different classification networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of regularization techniques and the analysis of learned features suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses correlation analysis, which is a common statistical technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
